{'title': 'AIA Extend Solidarity to Arrested Republican Activists - Anti Imperialist Action Ireland', 'time': '2023-02-25T11:20:18+00:00', 'description': 'Anti Imperialist Action Ireland extend our solidarity to the Republican activists arrested and to the families and communities enduring harassment and raids over recent days in Omagh and Coalisland Co. Tyrone by British Imperialist forces. The targeting of Republican political activists in this way is an attempt to intimidate Republicans into silence. This tactic has [&hellip;]', 'author': 'isrmedia', 'images': ['https://anti-imperialist-action-ireland.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/87235570-E58B-43E7-9F45-2246816549AF.jpeg'], 'text': '![](https://anti-imperialist-action-ireland.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/87235570-E58B-43E7-9F45-2246816549AF.jpeg)\n\nAnti Imperialist Action Ireland extend our solidarity to the Republicanactivists arrested and to the families and communities enduring harassment andraids over recent days in Omagh and Coalisland Co. Tyrone by BritishImperialist forces.\n\nThe targeting of Republican political activists in this way is an attempt tointimidate Republicans into silence. This tactic has failed in the past and itwill continue to fail now.\n\nBritain has no right to be in Ireland and no one describing themselves asRepublican should be offering the RUC or any other Brit Crown forces theirsupport for carrying out their ongoing war against republicans.\n\nBrit Militia’s are not welcome in Ireland! RUC/PSNI Out!', 'categories': ['AIA'], 'type': 'article', 'source': 'https://anti-imperialist-action-ireland.com/blog/2023/02/25/aia-extend-solidarity-to-arrested-republican-activists/'}